Create a responsive online job board website using WordPress for the backend and Elementor for the frontend design.
Implement user authentication and authorization allowing job seekers and employers to create accounts securely.
Design a clean, user-friendly UI using Bootstrap 5 for easy navigation and job search functionalities.
Use custom post types in WordPress to manage job listings, applications, and employer profiles effectively.
Create a searchable database of job listings with filtering options by category, location, salary range, and job type (full-time, part-time, freelance).
Implement a resume upload feature that allows job seekers to submit their resumes directly through the platform.
Design an application tracking system for job seekers to monitor their applications and receive updates from employers.
Create a company profile section where employers can showcase their business culture, values, and available positions.
Implement a review system that allows employees to rate their experiences with different companies, providing insights for other job seekers.
Design an analytics dashboard for employers to track the performance of their job postings, including views and applications received.
Create partnerships with local businesses or recruitment agencies to promote job listings and attract more users to the platform.
Implement multi-language support to cater to diverse job seekers in different regions.
Design an onboarding process with tutorials guiding new users through platform features and how to apply for jobs effectively.
Create personalized notifications for new job postings based on user preferences and saved searches.
Implement advanced search functionality allowing users to filter jobs by skills required, experience level, or industry.
Design user profiles where job seekers can manage their resumes, cover letters, preferences, and application history effectively.
Create integration with social media platforms allowing users to share job postings easily or apply using their LinkedIn profiles.
Implement push notifications for new job alerts or updates on application statuses within the app.
Design an FAQ section addressing common questions about using the job board and application processes.
Create a blog section featuring career advice, interview tips, and industry news relevant to job seekers and employers alike.
Implement a referral program that rewards users for referring friends or colleagues to the platform who successfully secure a job.
Design an interactive calendar feature that highlights upcoming career fairs or networking events in the area. 
Create an impact reporting feature that highlights success stories of users who found jobs through the platform. 
Implement data analytics to personalize recommendations based on user behavior and preferences. 
Design a custom API for third-party developers to integrate with the platform (e.g., HR software). 
Create a mobile app version of the site using React Native for on-the-go access to job listings. 
Implement an employer branding tool that allows companies to create targeted campaigns showcasing their workplace culture.
